%YAML 1.1
%TAG !u! tag:unity3d.com,2011:
--- !u!114 &11400000
MonoBehaviour:
  m_ObjectHideFlags: 0
  m_CorrespondingSourceObject: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabInstance: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabAsset: {fileID: 0}
  m_GameObject: {fileID: 0}
  m_Enabled: 1
  m_EditorHideFlags: 0
  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: 2bd16c723138d42428c3b24a7c4f950d, type: 3}
  m_Name: GlobalTipDatabase
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: Assembly-CSharp::GlobalTipDatabase
  tips:
  - tipId: general_welcome
    category: 0
    title: WELCOME TO HELL
    body: "You are a ghost trapped in Hell.\n\nExplore connected rooms, survive combat,
      complete dangerous challenges, collect Souls and XP, and search for clues that
      reveal the location of Hell\u2019s rulers.\n\nYour goal is simple: grow stronger,
      find the boss, and survive long enough to kill it."
    showOnlyOnce: 1
  - tipId: general_ledger
    category: 0
    title: SINNER'S LEDGER
    body: "Press L to open the Sinner\u2019s Ledger.\n\nThe Ledger shows your current
      stats, active challenge effects, owned shop items, and branch levels.\n\nOpen
      it whenever something changes and you want to understand what Hell has done
      to your build."
    showOnlyOnce: 1
  - tipId: general_movement_combat
    category: 0
    title: MOVEMENT AND ATTACK
    body: 'Move with WASD.


      Aim with the mouse. Your ghost attacks by firing
      ectoplasm toward your aim direction.


      Every shot costs AP. If your AP
      runs out, you cannot keep firing, so do not waste shots into walls or empty
      space. Let AP recover, reposition, and attack again when you have room to breathe.'
    showOnlyOnce: 1
  - tipId: general_hp_ap
    category: 0
    title: HP, AP, AND DMG
    body: 'HP is your life. If it reaches 0, you die and return to your last activated
      campfire.


      AP is your action fuel. Shooting and defensive actions use
      AP, so running out can leave you exposed.


      DMG shows how hard your ectoplasm
      shots hit. Level upgrades, challenge effects, and items can change these stats
      during a run.'
    showOnlyOnce: 1
  - tipId: general_disappear
    category: 0
    title: DISAPPEAR
    body: 'Disappear is your defensive escape.


      When active, you can avoid
      many dangerous attacks for a short time. Use it to slip through enemy pressure,
      survive boss attacks, or buy a moment when the room becomes too crowded.


      Disappear
      costs AP, so it is not free safety. If you spend all your AP attacking, you
      may not have enough left to defend yourself.'
    showOnlyOnce: 1
  - tipId: room_combat_first_enter
    category: 1
    title: COMBAT ROOMS
    body: 'Combat rooms lock you in until every enemy is defeated.


      Once the
      room is cleared, the doors open and you receive your rewards through combat:
      Souls for buying items and XP for leveling up.


      If you die, you return
      to your last campfire, but cleared and uncleared room states are remembered.'
    showOnlyOnce: 1
  - tipId: combat_enemy_variety
    category: 1
    title: ENEMY TYPES
    body: "Enemies do not all fight the same way.\n\nSome chase you down. Some keep
      distance and shoot. Some create explosions. Some defend themselves. Some summon
      more bodies into the room.\n\nWatch each enemy\u2019s behavior before committing.
      Hell punishes panic more than patience."
    showOnlyOnce: 1
  - tipId: room_campfire_first_enter
    category: 3
    title: CAMPFIRES
    body: 'Campfires are safe rooms.


      Entering a campfire activates it as
      your current checkpoint and restores your HP and AP to their current maximum
      values.


      When you die, this is where you return.'
    showOnlyOnce: 1
  - tipId: campfire_checkpoint_death
    category: 3
    title: CHECKPOINT RETURN
    body: 'Death does not end the run immediately.


      When you die, you return
      to your last activated campfire and lose some Souls. Use campfires to anchor
      your progress before pushing deeper into dangerous rooms.


      A Horsemen
      Ring can prevent death once if you own one.'
    showOnlyOnce: 1
  - tipId: room_trade_first_enter
    category: 6
    title: UNDER THE CROSSROADS
    body: 'Under the Crossroads is a safe merchant room.


      Spend Souls here
      to buy temporary tools for survival, burst damage, emergency control, or death
      prevention.


      These items can turn a doomed room into a winnable one,
      but only if you remember to use them.'
    showOnlyOnce: 1
  - tipId: trade_shop_items
    category: 6
    title: SHOP ITEMS
    body: "Bought items appear on the left side of the screen.\n\nUse hotkeys 1\u20134
      to activate active items:\n1: Chronos Spell\n2: Bloodlust Potion\n3: Ectoplasm
      Potion\n4: Horsemen Ring\n\nThe Horsemen Ring is passive. It activates automatically
      when you would die."
    showOnlyOnce: 1
  - tipId: trade_active_item_timers
    category: 6
    title: ITEM TIMERS
    body: 'Chronos, Bloodlust, and Ectoplasm are temporary effects.


      When
      one is active, a circular timer appears near the item HUD. The shrinking fill
      shows how much time remains.


      Using the same active item again refreshes
      its effect timer.'
    showOnlyOnce: 1
  - tipId: general_level_points
    category: 0
    title: LEVELS AND BRANCHES
    body: Defeating enemies gives XP.  When you gain enough XP, you level up and
      receive a branch point. Branch points are spent on upgrades that shape your
      build for the rest of the run.  Leveling does not automatically make every
      choice for you. You decide what kind of sinner you become.
    showOnlyOnce: 1
  - tipId: general_upgrade_menu
    category: 0
    title: UPGRADES
    body: "Press E during normal gameplay to open the upgrade menu.\n\nYou can spend
      branch points on four branches: Demon, Monster, Fallen God, and Hellhound.\n\nEach
      branch changes your run differently, so check your current build in the Sinner\u2019s
      Ledger with L."
    showOnlyOnce: 1
  - tipId: general_branch_identity
    category: 0
    title: BRANCH IDENTITY
    body: 'Demon improves offensive power and Disappear strength.

      Monster
      improves survivability through HP and AP.

      Fallen God gives balanced
      stat growth.

      Hellhound gives a chance to execute enemies when entering
      combat rooms.


      Choose branches based on how you want to survive Hell.'
    showOnlyOnce: 1
  - tipId: hostage_room_first_seen
    category: 4
    title: TRAPPED GHOSTS
    body: 'Some combat rooms contain trapped ghosts.


      If you find them, clear
      the room to break their prison. Rescued ghosts travel to your active campfire
      and gather there over time.


      Saving them does not just clear a room.
      It slowly changes your sanctuary.'
    showOnlyOnce: 1
  - tipId: hostage_campfire_population
    category: 4
    title: CAMPFIRE SPIRITS
    body: 'Rescued ghosts gather at your active campfire.


      Each campfire has
      limited space for spirits. If a campfire is full, new hostage rooms may stop
      appearing until another campfire becomes your active checkpoint.


      Your
      checkpoint is not only where you return. It is where the saved gather.'
    showOnlyOnce: 1
  - tipId: boss_clue_menu
    category: 7
    title: CLUES
    body: 'Press C to open the Clue Menu.


      Boss clues reveal hidden coordinates
      piece by piece. When enough clues are found, the boss room location becomes
      clear.


      Use the Clue Menu whenever you forget where the hunt is leading.'
    showOnlyOnce: 1
  - tipId: boss_gluttony_clues
    category: 7
    title: GLUTTONY CLUES
    body: 'Completing unique Gluttony Challenge rooms reveals the Gluttony Boss location.


      Only
      unique Gluttony rooms count. Repeating the same room will not reveal the same
      clue again.


      Find enough clues, and Hell will reveal where Gluttony
      is hiding.'
    showOnlyOnce: 1
  - tipId: boss_gluttony_room
    category: 7
    title: GLUTTONY BOSS
    body: 'Gluttony is not vulnerable all the time.


      He cycles through summoning
      Hellhounds, releasing an Eating Wave, and falling asleep. Attack him while
      he sleeps.


      The Eating Wave reduces your Max HP during the attempt unless
      you avoid it with Disappear. The Hellhounds are the main damage pressure, so
      decide when to clear them and when to shoot the boss.'
    showOnlyOnce: 1
  - tipId: boss_mvp_ending
    category: 7
    title: HUNGER CLUE
    body: 'Defeating Gluttony reveals the first clue toward Hunger, one of the Horsemen.


      This
      MVP ends with Gluttony, but the larger hunt continues beyond him: Sins, Horsemen,
      and finally Lucifer.


      For now, survive Gluttony. The next nightmare
      can wait.'
    showOnlyOnce: 1
  - tipId: general_attack_disappear_controls
    category: 0
    title: CONTROLS
    body: 'Use Left Mouse Click to shoot ectoplasm.


      Press Q to switch combat
      mode.


      Use Right Mouse Click to Disappear when you are in Defense mode.
      Disappear makes you avoid danger for a short time, but it costs AP.

'
    showOnlyOnce: 1
